               <interp inst="t18410823-2240" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/18410823"></interp>
               <interp inst="t18410823-2240" type="date" value="18410823"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18410823-2240-charge-1" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-2240-18410823 t18410823-2240-offence-1 t18410823-2240-verdict-1"></join>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18410823-2240-charge-2" targOrder="Y" targets="def2-2240-18410823 t18410823-2240-offence-1 t18410823-2240-verdict-2"></join>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18410823-2240-charge-3" targOrder="Y" targets="def3-2240-18410823 t18410823-2240-offence-1 t18410823-2240-verdict-3"></join>
               <p>2240. <hi rend="largeCaps">
                     <persName id="def1-2240-18410823" type="defendantName">
                        <interp inst="def1-2240-18410823" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="def1-2240-18410823" type="age" value="42"></interp>
                        <interp inst="def1-2240-18410823" type="surname" value="RICKETTS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="def1-2240-18410823" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>DANIEL RICKETTS</persName>,<persName id="def2-2240-18410823" type="defendantName">
                        <interp inst="def2-2240-18410823" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="def2-2240-18410823" type="age" value="29"></interp>
                        <interp inst="def2-2240-18410823" type="surname" value="SKIGGS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="def2-2240-18410823" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp> THOMAS SKIGGS</persName>
                  </hi>, and <persName id="def3-2240-18410823" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def3-2240-18410823" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def3-2240-18410823" type="age" value="32"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def3-2240-18410823" type="surname" value="BENNETT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def3-2240-18410823" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">WILLIAM BENNETT</hi>
                  </persName> were indicted for<rs id="t18410823-2240-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18410823-2240-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18410823-2240-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> stealing, on the <rs id="t18410823-cd-255" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18410823-2240-offence-1 t18410823-cd-255"></join>10th of July</rs>, 3 trusses of hay, value 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18410823-name-1364" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1364" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1364" type="surname" value="WOODHOUSE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1364" type="given" value="MICHAEL"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18410823-2240-offence-1 t18410823-name-1364"></join>Michael Woodhouse</persName>.—2nd <hi rend="smallCaps">COUNT</hi>, stating them to be the goods of <persName id="t18410823-name-1365" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1365" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1365" type="surname" value="GINGELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1365" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18410823-2240-offence-1 t18410823-name-1365"></join>James Gingell</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DOANE</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410823-name-1366" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1366" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1366" type="surname" value="WOODHOUSE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1366" type="given" value="MICHAEL"></interp>MICHAEL WOODHOUSE</persName>
                  </hi>. I gave directions to send two loads of hay to Whitechapel-market—Gingell was my salesman—I have a little boy named Ebenezer Woodhouse—Ricketts was my carter—it was his duty to carry the hay to Whitechapel.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CHAMBERS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> You are a farmer, and grow hay and clover? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—my hay-binder is not here—I know nothing about two loads being bound up—Gingell's business is to sell the hay—he pays me the money when I like to go after it—sometimes a month or two passes—he always passes me the bills of parcels back from the man that has it—I do not recollect the price at all—I expect the salesman to do the best he can for me—Ricketts has been in my service sixteen years—he was always honest for any thing I know—he lives in my house as in-door servant.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DOANE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Have you been paid for this hay? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, by Gingell.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410823-name-1367" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1367" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1367" type="surname" value="BYERS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1367" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM BYERS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the service of Mr. Gingell, a salesman in the hay market, Whitechapel. On the 10th of July, Mr. Banks, the ma<lb></lb>naging-man for Mr. Rhodes, came to purchase two loads of hay—there was a wagon of Mr. Woodhouse's, which had two loads on it—I sold it for two loads, seventy-two trusses—Ricketts and a little boy came with it—I promised to send this hay to Banks's, for Mr. Rhodes—I did not expect to be paid till he received it—Ricketts and the boy went with it—they were to go direct to Mr. Rhodes at Stoke Newington—they had no right to go any where else.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CHAMBERS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> You know the mode of this business? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—the hay-carts are driven into High-street, White<lb></lb>chapel, when a purchaser comes, and we make the bargain—I agreed to sell this for six guineas a load—I told Mr. Banks I could not take less—Rhodes had dealt with me before—they used to pay once in six weeks, or when we liked to take a bill—I cannot tell when they paid for it—it was a goodish bit after it was sold—perhaps a month.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410823-name-1368" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1368" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1368" type="surname" value="BANKS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1368" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM BANKS</persName>
                  </hi>.—I am foreman to Messrs. Rhodes. I purchased two loads of hay—they were to be delivered before I paid for them—they were to be sent to Stoke Newington. On Saturday morning, the 10th of July, I went and saw some clover—I asked Byers the price, he said, "Six gui<lb></lb>neas"—I desired him to send two loads to Stoke Newington—there were seventy-two trusses in two loads—I presumed he sent it home—I got home twenty minutes before twelve o'clock—when I got home, I found the wagon and hay had arrived—I saw Searing and Carswell, and in conse<lb></lb>quence of what Carswell said to me, I went to the station—I got Mr. Pritchard and an officer, and took Ricketts into custody for stealing three trusses of clover—I went with Pritchard to the Elephant public-house, and</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184108230174"></xptr>
               <p>saw Pritchard speak to Bennett, the ostler—after going into one place and another, I saw three trusses of clover—I said, "These are three I pur<lb></lb>chased this morning"—there was other hay of different descriptions— Pritchard asked how it came there—Bennett hemmed and hawed, and then said he purchased it last Thursday—these three trusses were worth 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Was not what you said that they were three you thought were yours? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, they looked like mine—it has turned out since that only two were of the same kind as mine—they are all three of the same quality—I speak from merely seeing it in the cart, and then looking at it in the stable.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CHAMBERS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> I suppose at Whitechapel, there are public-houses? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I seldom go into one, except to have a bit of bread and cheese—I cannot tell whether I did that morning—I cannot recollect Byers and I going to a public-house—it is not customary to bind the bargain—I agreed to give six guineas a load.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410823-name-1369" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1369" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1369" type="surname" value="SEARING"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1369" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH SEARING</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at Cheshunt, in Herts. On this Saturday, I was driving a horse and cart—I saw Woodhouse's wagon with two loads of hay—I saw Ricketts and the boy on the top, and Skiggs was driving the wagon—they stopped at the Elephant—Rickett's got off, and went with Skiggs into the house, and had some beer, Skiggs then came and took the fore horse, and Ricketts drove the hind horse, and turned down the street by the stable-door—I saw Bennett by the stable—I saw Skiggs undo the ropes—Ricketts got on the top, and took three trusses down, the first Bennett took in his arms, the next truss Ricketts set down on the ground—then he took the other down, and Ricketts spread the cloth over the remainder of the clover—then Bennett, Ricketts, and the boy came to the door, and Bennett gave Ricketts some money—I do not know how much.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> How many times have you been charged with felony? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Never.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410823-name-1370" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1370" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1370" type="surname" value="WOODHOUSE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1370" type="given" value="EBENEZER"></interp>EBENEZER WOODHOUSE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am nephew of Mr. Woodhouse. I am twelve years old—I came up with two loads of my uncle's hay on this occasion—Ricketts was the carman—after that I went with Ricketts to Mr. Rhodes's—before we got out of Whitechapel, Skiggs came to us—after he came up, Ricketts got on the top of the wagon, and Skiggs drove—they stopped at the Elephant, in the Kingsland-road—we stopped there, and Skiggs took the fore horse, and Ricketts drove the hind horse, and took the wagon down by the side of the public-house stable—I saw Ben<lb></lb>nett by the side of the stable—Skiggs undid the ropes, and Ricketts put the head of the tilt up, and then put three trusses of hay down—Bennett got them, and put them into the stable—Bennett and Ricketts had some drink, and Skiggs went on with the wagon—Bennett gave Ricketts some money, and then I went on after the wagon.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Where were you all the time? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> On the wagon—Skiggs drove it round into the high road again—I saw Mr. Searing behind with his cart—I did not tell any body about it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410823-name-1371" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1371" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1371" type="surname" value="CARSWELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1371" type="given" value="ALLAN"></interp>ALLAN CARSWELL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the service of Messrs. Rhodes—when the wagon arrived there were sixty-nine trusses—there ought to have been seventy-two—I remember Mr. Banks returning from the market before the prisoners left the yard—Skiggs was in the yard at the time.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CHAMBERS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What are you? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Assistant in</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184108230175"></xptr>
               <p>the yard—I count all the trusses, unless Mr. Bennett is there—the men were given in charge—Mr. Woodhouse saw the hay found at Bennett's.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410823-name-1372" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1372" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1372" type="surname" value="DANIELS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1372" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES DANIELS</persName>
                  </hi>. I accompanied the inspector to Messrs. Rhodes, and there took Ricketts into custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410823-name-1373" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1373" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1373" type="surname" value="PRITCHARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1373" type="given" value="BENJAMIN"></interp>BENJAMIN PRITCHARD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am an inspector of police—I went with Banks to the Elephant—I saw Bennett, who is ostler there—I asked him to allow me to go into his stable—he made no difficulty—I said I suspected there was hay that had been stolen—he opened the lock, and we found nothing there—he opened another stable—there were three trusses of hay, which Mr. Banks pointed out—there were other trusses of very different sort all together—Mr. Banks said, "How came they here; how long have you had them"—he hesitated, and said, "Oh, on Thursday."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410823-name-1374" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1374" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1374" type="surname" value="RICHARDS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1374" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS RICHARDS</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable N</hi> 208.) I took Skiggs—he asked what for, I told him—he said he would make them pay well for his time.</p>
               <p>(Bennett received a good character.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">RICKETTS—
<rs id="t18410823-2240-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-2240-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-2240-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>. Aged 42.—
<rs id="t18410823-2240-punishment-261" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18410823-2240-punishment-261" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18410823-2240-punishment-261" type="punishmentSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-2240-18410823 t18410823-2240-punishment-261"></join>Confined Three Months</rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">SKIGGS—
<rs id="t18410823-2240-verdict-2" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-2240-verdict-2" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-2240-verdict-2" type="verdictSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>. Aged 29.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">BENNETT—
<rs id="t18410823-2240-verdict-3" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-2240-verdict-3" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-2240-verdict-3" type="verdictSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>. Aged 32.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18410823-2240-punishment-262" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18410823-2240-punishment-262" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
